<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-585-499  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 585 499.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Nov 5 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New for IBM: Bechtel WalkThru animation software. (BechtelSoftware) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Buckler, Grant.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Bechtel Software Inc. (Product enhancement).andO;Product:   Walkthru (CAD software) (Product enhancement).andO;Topic:     Software PublishersEnhancementsAnimationComputer-aided designSoftware packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW FOR IBM: Bechtel Walkthru Animation Software 11/05/90 ACTON,MASSACHUSETTS, U.S.A., 1990 NOV 5 (NB) -- Bechtel Software has ported itsWalkThru design animation software to Silicon Graphics' new IrisVisiongraphics board for IBM and compatible PCs.andP;  The software previously ran onlyon Silicon Graphics Iris and IBM RISC/System 6000 workstations.andM;Bechtel says the move marks the first time personal computer users have hadaccess to real-time animation technology previously available only onhigh-end graphics workstations.andM;In a prepared statement, Bechtel Software President John Lucas called theannouncement &quot;a milestone in the evolution of engineering tools because itallows us to bring a powerful animation and visualization product likeWalkThru to the personal computer environment.&quot;andM;The software allows users to view 3-D computer models as though they alreadyexist in the real world.andP;  By loading model files onto WalkThru, users can seethe designs in fully shaded images and move around the model in real time,Bechtel said.andM;WalkThru is used for reviewing designs for correctness before construction tominimize change orders and reduce life cycle costs.andP;  It may also be used inbusiness development, training, and maintenance planning.andM;WalkThru works with the following CAD systems: Bechtel Software's own 3DM,GDS from McDonnell Douglas, Calma from Prime, IGDS from Intergraph,MicroStation from Bentley Systems, AES from IBM, CADAM from CADAM Inc., CATIAfrom Dassault Systems, AISYS from IASA, AutoCad from Autodesk, Dimension IIIfrom Prime Computervision, Ideas from SDRC, and IGES.andM;The DOS version of WalkThru requires an IBM Personal System/2 Model 70-A21 orequivalent with 120 megabytes of hard disk space and six megabytes ofrandom-access memory.andP;  A Unix version runs on an IBM PS/2 Model 80-A31 with320 megabytes of disk space and eight megabytes of RAM.andP;  Both versionsrequire an Intel 80387-25 math coprocessor, a three-button mouse, a VGAdisplay adapter and a high-resolution graphics monitor, said Lisa Boulais, aBechtel spokeswoman.andM;The software is priced at US$3,995.andP;  The 24-bit IrisVision board costsUS$4,995.andM;(Grant Buckler/19901031/1145PST/Press Contact: Lisa Boulais, Bechtel,508-635-0580)</TEXT></DOC>